  "title": "Revit Drafter[West/Proficient in Revit (BIM) and AutoCAD/Minimum Diploma/Certificate in Mechanical Engineering, Drafting]",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare and develop Revit (BIM) models and AutoCAD 2D drawings for mechanical systems.</li>\n  <li>Produce detailed production and shop drawings, including Bills of Materials (BOM), using AutoCAD and Inventor.</li>\n  <li>Prepare as-built drawings based on site installations and conduct site visits when required.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with project engineers, sales, and project teams to resolve design and drawing issues.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with consultants and clients to ensure compliance with design requirements and project specifications.</li>\n  <li>Participate in project meetings to provide support on drawing and design-related matters.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all drawings adhere to industry standards, codes, and company guidelines.</li>\n  <li>Willing to travel to Malaysia and perform overtime when required.</li>\n  <li>Undertake other ad-hoc drafting and design assignments as delegated by the superior.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p><em>Qualification</em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum Diploma/Certificate in Mechanical Engineering, Drafting, or a related discipline.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Experience</em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>2–3 years of relevant working experience.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Skills</em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Proficient in Revit (BIM) and AutoCAD.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of Inventor is an advantage.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Office applications.</li>\n  <li>Strong technical and communication skills.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
